<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Thereby" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Thereby,</orth> 1) annexed to that: <cit><quote>t. hangs a tale,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 4, 159</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.28" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 1, 8</bibl>.<lb />2) by that, by means of that: <cit><quote>from fairest creatures we desire increase, that t. beauty's rose might never die,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. I, 2</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.162" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 162</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.283" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 283</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.337" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 337</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.276" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 276</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.218" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 218</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.119" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.115" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.187" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.218" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 218</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 5, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.207" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.4.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 4, 5</bibl>. <cit><quote>she carved thee for her seal, and meant t. thou shouldst print more,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 11.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 11, 13</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 1, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 84</bibl>.
